The bookmark is unmutable after it is created in other languages. The methods that we want to add are aiming to provide a way for a user to get a string set out and then reconstruct a Bookmark back from the string set.

This `update` method here is more like a method to modify the current Bookmark.
For example the Java driver has the following methods:
```
    /**
     * Returns a read-only set of bookmark strings that this bookmark instance identifies.
     */
    Set<String> values();

    /**
     * Reconstruct bookmark from bookmarks string values.
     * @param values values obtained from a previous bookmark.
     * @return A bookmark.
     */
    static Bookmark from( Set<String> values )
    {
        return InternalBookmark.parse( values );
    }
```
We on purpose to make `values` to return a read-only set. And also the `from` method to be static so that no one could ever modify the bookmark values after they are created.

